CSRF Protection
-> Introduction
-> An Explanation Of The Vulnerability
-> Laravel automatically generates a CSRF "token" for each active user session managed by the application.
-> stored in the user's session and changes each time the session is regenerated
-> access via csrf_token() helper method
-> in HTML FORM via _token hidden field or @csrf blade syntax 
-> VerifyCsrfToken middleware automatically
-> Excluding URIs From CSRF Protection : $except property of VerifyCsrfToken middleware
-> X-CSRF-Token
-> X-XSRF-Token